cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is about a novel neural network architecture for computer vision tasks, specifically image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the size-accuracy trade-off of the proposed architecture, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) in the proposed architecture may make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
